<TITLE> Iajuddin off to US </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com)  President Iajuddin Ahmed left for New York Tuesday on an official seven-day visit to the US which will include engagements in Ohio and New Orleans. The president will visit the Ohio Agriculture Research Centre on Nov 1 where he will deliver a lecture on the state of the education system in Bangladesh. The following morning Iajuddin will meet the Mayor of Columbus prior to a visit to the Noor Islamic Cultural Centre in Dublin. In the afternoon he will deliver a lecture at the Ohio State University on global warming issues in the context of Bangladesh. The president is scheduled to meet the governor of Ohio on Nov 3 prior to his departure for New Orleans the next day where he will attend a reception hosted by the Soil Science Society of America. Iajuddin will conclude his tour of New Orleans on Nov 6 when he flies to New York before returning to Dhaka on Nov 8. The president's wife Anwara Begum accompanies her husband with his military secretary and other aides. bdn
